<plot>She-Bop is about power, rage and seizing control of your life. The star of the film in the film is cartoon Kali, the great destroyer/creator goddess. She-Bop combines drawings on index cards and puppets, abstraction and character animation. It is based on a poem by Carolyn Myers, interpreted and performed by jazz singer Carolyn Lochert Curtis.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?491767</url></doc>
